[{"location":"#BartIO-documentation","page":"Home","title":"BartIO documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Calling-BART-functions","page":"Home","title":"Calling BART functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Requirements","page":"Home","title":"Requirements","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"BART -> compiled\nbartpy -> does not required to be installed","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In order to call bart, the new python wrapper needs to be install in the pycall environment with :","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"initBart(path2bart::String,path2bartpy::String)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Alternatively","page":"Home","title":"Alternatively","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"BART can be called from the terminal :","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"run(`bart version`)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"or with the standard wrapper available in the bart/python","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"py\"\"\"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, \"/Users/aurelien/Documents/SOFTWARE/bart/python/\")\n\"\"\"\n\nbart = pyimport(\"bart\")[\"bart\"]\n\nbart(0,\"version\")\nimg = bart(1,\"phantom -x64\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#IO-to-BART-files","page":"Home","title":"IO to BART files","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If you want to call the bart with the terminal you need to write/read the BART files using  :","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"readcfl\nwritecfl","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"readcfl(filename::String)","category":"page"},{"location":"#BartIO.readcfl-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","title":"BartIO.readcfl","text":"readcfl(filename::String)\n\nreadcfl(filename(no extension)) -> Array{ComplexF32,N} where N is defined the filename.hdr file\nreadcfl(filename.cfl) -> Array{ComplexF32,N} where N is defined the filename.hdr file\nreadcfl(filename.hdr) -> Array{ComplexF32,N} where N is defined the filename.hdr file\n\nReads complex data from files created by the Berkeley Advanced Reconstruction Toolbox (BART). The output is an Array of ComplexF32 with the dimensions stored in a .hdr file.\n\nParameters:\n\nfilename:   path and filename of the cfl and hdr files, which can either be without extension, end on .cfl, or end on .hdr\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"writecfl(filename::String,dataCfl::Array{ComplexF32})","category":"page"},{"location":"#BartIO.writecfl-Tuple{String, Array{ComplexF32, N} where N}","page":"Home","title":"BartIO.writecfl","text":"writecfl(filename::String,dataCfl::Array{ComplexF32})\n\nwritecfl(filename(no extension),Array{ComplexF32})\nwritecfl(filename.cfl, Array{ComplexF32})\nwritecfl(filename.hdr,Array{ComplexF32})\n\nWrite complex data to files following the convention of the Berkeley Advanced Reconstruction Toolbox (BART). The input is an Array of ComplexF32 with the dimensions stored in a .hdr file.\n\nParameters:\n\nfilename:   path and filename of the cfl and hdr files, which can either be without extension, end on .cfl, or end on .hdr\nArray{ComplexF32,N}:   Array of ComplexF32 corresponding to image/k-space\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
